WEBVTT

00:01.610 --> 00:02.741
PREVIOUSLY
ON "THE MENTALIST"...

00:02.785 --> 00:04.569
LENA'S ON A SHORT LIST
FOR A POSITION

00:04.613 --> 00:06.136
IN THE COMMERCE DEPARTMENT
IN D.C.

00:06.180 --> 00:07.746
IT'S NOT A DONE DEAL YET.

00:07.790 --> 00:09.270
I HAVE TO BE CONFIRMED,
AND THAT COULD TAKE MONTHS.

00:09.313 --> 00:11.837
THIS IS BILL PETERSON,
SAN ANTONIO D.E.A.

00:11.881 --> 00:13.578
WHAT DOES THIS GUY PETERSON
HAVE ON YOU?

00:13.622 --> 00:15.450
WHEN I WAS YOUR BOSS
AT RIO BRAVO,

00:15.493 --> 00:16.886
I HAD YOUR BACK.

00:16.929 --> 00:18.714
YOU TELLING ME YOU DON'T
HAVE MINE NOW?

00:18.757 --> 00:21.021
JANE, I'M ON THE 6th FLOOR NOW.

00:21.064 --> 00:24.067
LISBON, IT LOOKS LIKE HE MAY BE
AT THE OTHER END. KEEP GOING.

00:24.111 --> 00:25.590
YOU TOOK ME OFF ON PURPOSE.

00:25.634 --> 00:27.201
YOU HAVE TO LET ME
DO MY JOB.

00:27.244 --> 00:29.638
IF YOU CAN'T,
HOW DO WE WORK TOGETHER?

00:29.681 --> 00:32.162
PETERSON CAN END MY CAREER.
I CAN GO TO PRISON.

00:32.206 --> 00:35.252
ANY MENTION OF THIS
COULD END THINGS FOR LENA

00:35.296 --> 00:36.775
BEFORE IT EVEN STARTS.

00:36.819 --> 00:38.038
WELL, YOU CAN'T LET HIM DO IT.

00:38.081 --> 00:40.127
IT'S OVER FOR YOU.
AND YOUR WIFE.

00:40.170 --> 00:41.650
I'M GONNA SEE TO THAT.

00:43.173 --> 00:45.871
[ SHOVELS DIGGING ]

00:45.915 --> 00:49.397
Men: [ SPEAKING SPANISH ]

00:49.440 --> 00:51.355
[ CREAKING ]

00:54.054 --> 00:57.100
[ MEN GRUNTING,
SPEAKING SPANISH ]

00:57.144 --> 00:59.537
Man: [ SPEAKS SPANISH ]

01:02.149 --> 01:03.715
[ SPEAKS SPANISH ]

01:05.456 --> 01:07.067
[ CREAKING ]

01:26.695 --> 01:28.436
SEE?

01:34.659 --> 01:36.922
[ SAW WHIRRING ]

01:44.408 --> 01:46.715
Jane: EVERYTHING TURNED OUT
EXACTLY AS WE PLANNED.

01:46.758 --> 01:48.934
I KNOW.NO ONE WAS HURT.

01:48.978 --> 01:50.240
I KNOW.

01:50.284 --> 01:51.589
WELL, EXCEPT THE BAD GUY,
OF COURSE,

01:51.633 --> 01:53.374
BUT HE WAS AN ASSASSIN.

01:53.417 --> 01:55.202
I UNDERSTAND.
MISSION ACCOMPLISHED.

01:55.245 --> 01:56.768
BUT IN THE MIDDLE
OF OUR MISSION

01:56.812 --> 01:58.118
YOU DIRECTED ME
TO GO SOMEWHERE

01:58.161 --> 01:59.510
THAT HAD NOTHING TO DO
WITH THE MISSION.

01:59.554 --> 02:01.208
YEAH, I WAS CONCERNED
ABOUT YOUR SAFETY.

02:01.251 --> 02:03.297
YOU DON'T GET IT.I DON'T GET WHAT?

02:03.340 --> 02:04.820
I'M AN F.B.I. AGENT.

02:04.863 --> 02:06.169
UH, I THINK I DO GET THAT.[ PHONE RINGING ]

02:06.213 --> 02:08.040
NO, I DON'T THINK YOU DO.EXCUSE ME.

02:08.084 --> 02:10.173
[ RINGS ]WILEY?

02:10.217 --> 02:12.349
YOU ASKED ME TO KEEP TABS
ON PETERSON,

02:12.393 --> 02:14.395
LET YOU KNOW IF HE'S MAKING
ANY SUSPICIOUS MOVES.

02:14.438 --> 02:16.875
Yeah. What's he done?ACCORDING TO HIS
CREDIT CARD RECORD,

02:16.919 --> 02:19.095
TWO DAYS AGO HE BOUGHT
A PLANE TICKET TO MEXICO.

02:19.139 --> 02:20.488
He flew there
this morning.

02:20.531 --> 02:22.229
WELL, HE MIGHT HAVE GONE
DOWN THERE FOR WORK.

02:22.272 --> 02:24.753
I CHECKED. HIS OFFICE SAID HE'S
AT A CONFERENCE IN ST. PAUL.

02:24.796 --> 02:26.494
OKAY, WELL,
COULD YOU LOOK INTO

02:26.537 --> 02:28.539
PETERSON'S
PHONE RECORDS FOR US?

02:28.583 --> 02:30.150
WE'LL BE RIGHT IN.

02:30.193 --> 02:31.542
WHAT AM I LOOKING FOR?

02:31.586 --> 02:35.155
WELL, SOMETHING FISHY.Fishy. Got it.

02:35.198 --> 02:36.765
IS THAT ABOUT ABBOTT?

02:36.808 --> 02:38.941
SOUNDS LIKE IT.WELL, WHAT ARE WE
GONNA DO?

02:38.984 --> 02:40.464
WHATEVER WE CAN.

02:40.508 --> 02:41.944
[ Lowered voice ]
PETERSON'S CHECKED INTO A HOTEL

02:41.987 --> 02:43.467
JUST OUTSIDE RIO BRAVO.

02:43.511 --> 02:45.426
THAT'S WHERE HE WORKED
WITH ABBOTT, RIGHT?

02:45.469 --> 02:48.211
[ Lowered voice ]
YEAH, TEN YEARS AGO.I CHECKED HIS PHONE RECORD.

02:48.255 --> 02:50.082
THE ONLY CALL THAT STUCK OUT

02:50.126 --> 02:52.346
WAS TO A SAN ANTONIO
CONGRESSMAN THIS AFTERNOON --

02:52.389 --> 02:54.217
REPRESENTATIVE JULES BLATT.

02:54.261 --> 02:55.827
I'VE HEARD OF HIM.

02:55.871 --> 02:57.916
HE'S A NOBODY TRYING TO MAKE
A NAME FOR HIMSELF.

02:57.960 --> 02:59.570
[ Lowered voice ]
WELL, IF HE COULD BLOCK

02:59.614 --> 03:01.659
LENA ABBOTT'S CONFIRMATION,
IT WOULD BUFF HIS REPUTATION

03:01.703 --> 03:03.226
IN CERTAIN CIRCLES,
WOULDN'T IT?

03:03.270 --> 03:05.620
HOW WOULD PETERSON GOING
TO RIO BRAVO HELP THAT?

03:05.663 --> 03:07.839
I DON'T KNOW. THE HEARINGS
START IN FOUR DAYS,

03:07.883 --> 03:09.493
SO IF PETERSON WANTS
TO MAKE TROUBLE,

03:09.537 --> 03:10.886
NOW IS THE TIME TO DO IT.

03:10.929 --> 03:12.279
WELL, WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

03:12.322 --> 03:15.020
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO
ABOUT WHAT?

03:17.936 --> 03:19.590
WHY IS EVERYONE WHISPERING?

03:21.679 --> 03:23.768
HOW DO YOU KNOW ABOUT
ALL THIS?

03:23.812 --> 03:27.076
WYLIE'S KEEPING TABS
ON PETERSON.

03:27.119 --> 03:28.991
AND YOU BROUGHT WYLIE
INTO IT?

03:29.034 --> 03:30.949
WELL, I MENTIONED THAT
PETERSON MIGHT BE

03:30.993 --> 03:32.168
MAKING SOME TROUBLE.

03:32.212 --> 03:33.735
HE VOLUNTEERED.

03:33.778 --> 03:35.432
THE KID WOULDN'T TAKE NO
FOR AN ANSWER.

03:35.476 --> 03:37.565
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA WHAT
PETERSON IS DOING IN RIO BRAVO?

03:37.608 --> 03:39.741
[ CHUCKLES DRYLY ]

03:39.784 --> 03:41.612
PETERSON'S CAREFUL.

03:41.656 --> 03:43.179
HE WOULDN'T MAKE
ANY ACCUSATIONS

03:43.223 --> 03:45.790
IF HE DIDN'T HAVE
THE EVIDENCE TO BACK IT UP.

03:45.834 --> 03:48.315
I SHOT A MAN.

03:48.358 --> 03:50.665
BULLET'S IN THE BODY.

03:50.708 --> 03:54.234
PETERSON FOUND THE CORPSE,
DUG OUT THE BULLET,

03:54.277 --> 03:56.279
ALL HE'S GOT TO DO IS
SUBPOENA THE GUN,

03:56.323 --> 03:58.716
AND...THAT'S GAME OVER.

04:00.370 --> 04:01.676
I NEED TO CALL LENA.

04:01.719 --> 04:04.331
MM.

04:04.374 --> 04:06.246
I'LL LET YOU DO THAT.

04:11.642 --> 04:13.470
WHAT DOES HE THINK
PETERSON HAS ON HIM?

04:13.514 --> 04:15.864
THE BULLET.WELL, IF HE DOES,
THEN ABBOTT'S TOAST.

04:15.907 --> 04:17.518
THAT'S A LITTLE
PESSIMISTIC.

04:17.561 --> 04:19.302
BUT THIS ISN'T JUST ABOUT
LENA'S CONFIRMATION.

04:19.346 --> 04:21.652
ABBOTT WILL LOSE HIS JOB.
HE COULD GO TO PRISON.

04:21.696 --> 04:24.002
I DON'T THINK THAT'S
GONNA HAPPEN.WHY NOT?

04:24.046 --> 04:26.962
WE'LL PREVENT IT.IN FOUR DAYS? HOW?

04:27.005 --> 04:29.791
I'M NOT QUITE SURE YET.

04:29.834 --> 04:31.880
JANE, THIS IS SERIOUS.

04:31.923 --> 04:35.971
I KNOW. DON'T YOU LOVE IT
WHEN THE STAKES ARE HIGH?

04:36.014 --> 04:38.843
♪♪♪

04:38.887 --> 04:41.933
--Captions by VITAC--

04:46.286 --> 04:48.505
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

04:48.549 --> 04:50.377
I CAME AS SOON AS I COULD.

04:50.420 --> 04:52.640
THANKS FOR COMING, HONEY.

04:52.683 --> 04:54.206
[ SIGHS ]

04:55.251 --> 04:57.340
LET'S TALK IN MY OFFICE.

04:58.776 --> 05:00.343
PETERSON?

05:00.387 --> 05:02.345
YES.

05:02.389 --> 05:03.999
YOU'RE SURE HE HAS
THE EVIDENCE?

05:04.042 --> 05:05.392
SURE ENOUGH.

05:05.435 --> 05:07.394
LOOK, BABY, I AM SO SORRY.

05:07.437 --> 05:09.309
I SHOULD HAVE TOLD YOU
EVERYTHING FROM THE START.DON'T SAY THAT.

05:09.352 --> 05:11.963
NO, NO, NO, IT'S MY FAULT.
I REALLY LET YOU DOWN.

05:12.007 --> 05:14.226
DO NOT SAY THAT.

05:14.270 --> 05:16.446
YOU DON'T HAVE TO APOLOGIZE,
NOT TO ME.

05:16.490 --> 05:18.796
NOT TO ANYONE.

05:18.840 --> 05:20.581
THAT THIS PERSON WOULD
TRY TO BRING YOU DOWN

05:20.624 --> 05:22.365
MAKES ME SO ANGRY.

05:24.149 --> 05:26.761
THIS IS SIMPLE.
I'LL WITHDRAW MY NAME.
NO.

05:26.804 --> 05:29.241
I DON'T WANT THE JOB IF THIS IS
WHAT IT TAKES TO GET IT.

05:29.285 --> 05:32.288
LOOK, I'M NOT GONNA HAVE YOU
QUIT BECAUSE OF ME. OKAY?

05:32.332 --> 05:34.682
NOW, I-I'LL TELL PETERSON
I'LL RESIGN.

05:34.725 --> 05:36.031
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

05:36.074 --> 05:38.381
WE CAN JUST GO ALONG
WITH THE SAME STORY

05:38.425 --> 05:41.558
THAT WE'RE SEPARATED,
AND MAYBE --[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

05:41.602 --> 05:43.473
EXCUSE ME?JANE, COULD YOU PLEASE
JUST GIVE US A MINUTE, PLEASE?

05:43.517 --> 05:45.606
YEAH, I WOULD, BUT TIME
IS SHORT, AND I'M GUESSING

05:45.649 --> 05:47.521
THAT EACH OF YOU IS OFFERING
TO FALL ON YOUR SWORD

05:47.564 --> 05:49.349
FOR THE OTHER, WHICH IS VERY
LOVING AND ADMIRABLE,

05:49.392 --> 05:52.047
BUT I DON'T THINK IT'LL WORK.WHY NOT?

05:52.090 --> 05:54.266
BECAUSE PETERSON IS RUTHLESS
AND DETERMINED,

05:54.310 --> 05:56.878
AND HE WON'T STOP UNTIL
HE'S DESTROYED BOTH OF YOU.

05:56.921 --> 05:58.488
NOW WE KNEW HE WAS GONNA
MAKE A MOVE LIKE THIS

05:58.532 --> 05:59.837
SOONER OR LATER.

05:59.881 --> 06:01.448
NOW IT IS TIME FOR US
TO MAKE OUR MOVE.

06:01.491 --> 06:02.971
WHICH IS WHAT, EXACTLY?

06:03.014 --> 06:04.755
THE HEARINGS ARE IN THREE DAYS.

06:04.799 --> 06:06.627
WELL, I THINK I CAN
COME UP WITH SOMETHING

06:06.670 --> 06:09.369
IF...YOU BOTH WANT ME INVOLVED.

06:09.412 --> 06:11.371
NO, NO, THIS IS --

06:11.414 --> 06:12.981
THIS IS NOT YOUR PROBLEM.WAIT A MINUTE.

06:13.024 --> 06:14.635
DENNIS TELLS ME YOU HAVE
ONE OF THE TRICKIEST

06:14.678 --> 06:16.201
AND MOST DEVIOUS MINDS
HE'S WORKED WITH.

06:16.245 --> 06:18.160
HE DID, DID HE? AH.

06:18.203 --> 06:20.554
WELL, I DIDN'T COME HERE TO BE
FLATTERED, BUT, PLEASE, GO ON.

06:20.597 --> 06:22.773
HE ALSO SAYS YOU'RE HIS FRIEND

06:22.817 --> 06:24.688
AND THAT HE WOULD TRUST YOU
WITH HIS LIFE.

06:26.168 --> 06:28.953
CAN YOU REALLY HELP?I THINK SO.

06:29.998 --> 06:32.435
[ EXHALES ] DENNIS.

06:33.610 --> 06:35.786
WHAT DO YOU HAVE IN MIND?

06:35.830 --> 06:38.180
I CAN'T TELL YOU.

06:38.223 --> 06:40.661
WE NEED YOUR HANDS
TO BE CLEAN.

06:40.704 --> 06:42.924
DENIABILITY AND SUCH.

06:49.670 --> 06:52.586
OKAY, WE'LL DO IT YOUR WAY.

06:52.629 --> 06:54.588
EXCELLENT.

06:57.199 --> 06:59.288
HEY, ANY UPDATES?

06:59.331 --> 07:00.942
PETERSON ARRIVED BACK
IN SAN ANTONIO TWO HOURS AGO.

07:00.985 --> 07:02.770
HAS HE HAD ANY MORE CONTACT
WITH CONGRESSMAN BLATT?

07:02.813 --> 07:04.380
NO, IT'S JUST THE ONE
PHONE CALL YESTERDAY.

07:04.424 --> 07:05.816
IT LASTED 30 SECONDS.

07:05.860 --> 07:06.948
IT WAS PROBABLY JUST
A VOICE MAIL MESSAGE.

07:06.991 --> 07:08.906
I HEAR ABBOTT'S IN TROUBLE.

07:08.950 --> 07:10.778
I'M NOT VERY GOOD
AT KEEPING SECRETS.

07:10.821 --> 07:12.344
GOOD THING
YOU'RE IN THE F.B.I.

07:12.388 --> 07:13.737
WHAT ARE WE DOING ABOUT IT?

07:13.781 --> 07:15.565
JANE'S COMING UP WITH
A PLAN RIGHT NOW.

07:15.609 --> 07:17.524
YOU MIGHT WANT TO THINK TWICE
BEFORE GETTING IN ON THIS ONE.

07:17.567 --> 07:19.439
BOTH OF YOU.

07:19.482 --> 07:21.441
I HAVE A FEELING WE'RE GONNA BE
PRETTY FAR OUTSIDE THE LINES.

07:21.484 --> 07:23.181
WELL, JANE HAD ME PRETEND
TO KILL A GUY ONCE.

07:23.225 --> 07:24.879
ARE WE GOING FURTHER OUTSIDE
THE LINES THAN THAT?

07:24.922 --> 07:26.446
PROBABLY NOT.

07:26.489 --> 07:28.099
THEN I'M GOOD.

07:28.143 --> 07:30.406
ME, TOO.

07:30.450 --> 07:31.712
LET'S TAKE THIS
OUT OF THE BULLPEN.

07:35.367 --> 07:38.327
WHAT DID ABBOTT SAY?ALL SYSTEMS GO.

07:38.370 --> 07:40.460
GREAT. SO WHAT DO YOU
GOT, WYLIE?

07:40.503 --> 07:43.027
BILL PETERSON IS 55 YEARS OLD.

07:43.071 --> 07:45.639
HE'S BEEN A D.E.A. AGENT
FOR 27 YEARS.

07:45.682 --> 07:49.294
MARRIED BRIEFLY IN HIS 30s.
HIS EX-WIFE LIVES IN TACOMA.

07:49.338 --> 07:50.382
NO KIDS, NO LIVING RELATIVES.

07:50.426 --> 07:51.688
WHAT DOES HE LIKE DOING?

07:51.732 --> 07:53.777
WORK, MOSTLY.
PLAYS A LITTLE TENNIS,

07:53.821 --> 07:55.823
GOES SCUBA-DIVING
IN THE CARIBBEAN.

07:55.866 --> 07:58.086
BASED ON WHAT HE BUYS
AT THE LOCAL LIQUOR STORE,

07:58.129 --> 08:00.915
HE'S A WINE SNOB.HMM. INTERESTING.

08:00.958 --> 08:02.830
WHY?

08:02.873 --> 08:04.919
OBVIOUSLY HE'S AS CORRUPT
AS THE DAY IS LONG.WHY OBVIOUSLY?

08:04.962 --> 08:07.269
WELL, A MAN THAT LIKES TENNIS,
TRAVEL, AND A GOOD BORDEAUX

08:07.312 --> 08:08.879
ISN'T RETIRING
ON A GOVERNMENT PENSION.

08:08.923 --> 08:11.012
HE HAS SOME LOOT STASHED
SOMEPLACE.

08:11.055 --> 08:13.971
WE NEED TO FIND IT.WHAT ABOUT THE EVIDENCE
PETERSON FOUND IN MEXICO?

08:14.015 --> 08:15.625
THE BULLET -- WHAT ARE WE
GONNA DO ABOUT THAT?

08:15.669 --> 08:17.322
I'LL TAKE CARE OF THE BULLET.
YOU DIG DOWN ON PETERSON.

08:17.366 --> 08:19.281
HE'S BEEN A D.E.A. AGENT
FOR 30 YEARS.

08:19.324 --> 08:20.848
THERE'S A TON OF WAYS
HE COULD BE STEALING.

08:20.891 --> 08:22.545
HE COULD BE TAKING PAYOFFS
FROM A CARTEL,

08:22.589 --> 08:23.720
HE COULD BE SELLING
THE DRUGS HIMSELF.

08:23.764 --> 08:25.592
YEAH, LOOK INTO STUFF LIKE THAT.

08:25.635 --> 08:28.377
I HAVE TO GO MAKE SOME CALLS
AND CATCH UP WITH AN OLD FRIEND.

08:45.481 --> 08:48.223
HI.WE CATCH A CASE?

08:48.266 --> 08:50.399
NO.WHAT ARE YOU ALL WORKING ON?

08:50.442 --> 08:51.618
NOTHING.

08:51.661 --> 08:53.010
SURE LOOKS LIKE SOMETHING.

08:53.054 --> 08:54.403
ANYTHING I CAN DO
TO HELP?YEAH.

08:54.446 --> 08:56.579
YOU CAN HOLD DOWN THE FORT
OUT HERE.

08:56.623 --> 08:59.234
UH--
DID I DO SOMETHING WRONG?

08:59.277 --> 09:01.541
NO. JUST STAY OUT HERE,
OKAY?

09:11.551 --> 09:13.901
MR. BARSOCKY.

09:13.944 --> 09:16.338
YOU CRAZY CIRCUS FREAK.

09:16.381 --> 09:19.167
AWW! PATRICK JANE,
YOU SON OF A BITCH.

09:19.210 --> 09:20.951
LOOKING GOOD, PETE.
VERY RELAXED.

09:20.995 --> 09:22.997
WELL, I'M AS A FAT
AND WRINKLED

09:23.040 --> 09:25.782
AS DAISY THE AMAZING ELEPHANT,
BUT THANKS.

09:25.826 --> 09:28.785
AND THANKS FOR PAVING THE WAY
TO AUSTIN.

09:28.829 --> 09:31.005
FIRST CLASS TICKETS
AND EVERYTHING.

09:31.048 --> 09:33.268
YOU SHOULD SEE THAT
HOTEL ROOM YOU PAID FOR.

09:33.311 --> 09:36.010
WELL, THAT IS MY PLEASURE,
PETE. HOW'S THINGS?

09:36.053 --> 09:40.318
YOU KNOW. LOOKING FOR RUBES
TO FLEECE. YOU?

09:40.362 --> 09:43.191
I'M -- I'M SEEING SOMEONE
AT THE MOMENT, ACTUALLY.

09:43.234 --> 09:45.106
YOU DOG.

09:45.149 --> 09:46.934
WAIT, IS IT THAT PRETTY
BRUNETTE THAT CAME AROUND

09:46.977 --> 09:48.588
WITH YOU A COUPLE YEARS
AGO -- THE COP?

09:48.631 --> 09:50.198
AS A MATTER OF FACT, IT IS.

09:50.241 --> 09:52.374
I KNEW IT. I COULD TELL
SHE WAS SWEET ON YOU.

09:52.417 --> 09:54.637
WELL, SHE'S A LITTLE CRANKY
WITH ME RIGHT NOW.

09:54.681 --> 09:57.727
WOMEN. WHO GETS 'EM?

09:57.771 --> 10:01.035
BUT I'M HAPPY TO HEAR IT.

10:01.078 --> 10:03.211
YOU SHOULD HAVE SOMEONE,
PATRICK.

10:03.254 --> 10:06.127
YOU DESERVE TO BE HAPPY.THANK YOU.

10:06.170 --> 10:09.696
MAYBE IT'S TIME,
YOU KNOW?

10:09.739 --> 10:11.480
TAKE THE RING OFF.

10:11.523 --> 10:15.136
NO SHAME IN MOVING ON.
ANGELA WOULD WANT YOU TO.

10:15.179 --> 10:17.225
YEAH. THANKS, PETE.
I NEED A FAVOR.

10:17.268 --> 10:18.966
I HAVE A FRIEND WHO'S
IN A LITTLE TROUBLE

10:19.009 --> 10:21.011
WITH THE LAW, AND I WANT
TO GET HIM OUT OF IT.

10:21.055 --> 10:23.579
SOUNDS LIKE FUN TO ME.THAT'S WHAT I THOUGHT.

10:23.623 --> 10:25.668
SO, HERE'S THE GAG...

10:25.712 --> 10:28.279
THAT'S ALL FINE, BUT I NEED
THOSE OTHER FILES.

10:29.454 --> 10:31.979
YEAH, GET ME THE -- THE SECOND
QUARTER ARREST FIGURES

10:32.022 --> 10:34.721
ON MY DESK IN THE MORNING,
ALL RIGHT?

10:34.764 --> 10:36.723
YEAH. SEE YOU THEN.Woman: SIR? EXCUSE ME?

10:36.766 --> 10:39.377
[ PHONE BEEPS ]THIS IS A PRIVATE CLUB.
YOU CAN'T -- SIR?

10:40.465 --> 10:41.902
SIR?WHO LET YOU IN?

10:41.945 --> 10:43.817
OH, I'M JUST TAKING
A LITTLE LOOK AROUND,

10:43.860 --> 10:45.732
THINKING ABOUT MEMBERSHIP.IS THAT SUPPOSED TO BE
AMUSING?

10:45.775 --> 10:47.951
MR. PETERSON, THIS MAN SAID
THAT HE WAS FROM YOUR OFFICE.

10:47.995 --> 10:49.518
IS THERE A PROBLEM?

10:49.561 --> 10:51.259
IT'S FINE, STACEY.

10:51.302 --> 10:54.044
STACEY, MR. PETERSON AND I
GO WAY BACK. THANK YOU.

10:54.088 --> 10:55.655
[ SIGHS ]

10:55.698 --> 10:57.526
HOW WAS YOUR LITTLE TRIP
DOWN TO RIO BRAVO?

10:57.569 --> 10:59.702
YOU KNOW ABOUT THAT?OF COURSE I DO.

10:59.746 --> 11:01.225
YOU THINK I'M GONNA SIT BACK

11:01.269 --> 11:02.705
AND WATCH YOU DESTROY
DENNIS ABBOTT?

11:02.749 --> 11:04.533
I'M NOT TRYING TO DESTROY
ANYONE.

11:04.576 --> 11:07.492
I'M AFTER JUSTICE.

11:07.536 --> 11:09.494
DENNIS ABBOTT MURDERED
A MAN IN COLD BLOOD.

11:09.538 --> 11:13.020
A COMMANDER OF ONE OF THE
LARGEST DRUG CARTELS IN MEXICO.

11:13.063 --> 11:14.499
MURDERED HIM NONETHELESS.

11:14.543 --> 11:17.067
DON'T YOU HAVE BETTER
THINGS TO DO, PETERSON?

11:17.111 --> 11:19.853
LIKE UPDATE YOUR TENNIS GEAR?
WHAT IS THIS?

11:19.896 --> 11:23.073
OH, IT'S VELOUR.
HMM.

11:23.117 --> 11:25.772
LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING,
JANE.

11:25.815 --> 11:29.166
I DON'T GIVE A RAT'S ASS
ABOUT DENNIS ABBOTT.

11:29.210 --> 11:30.428
I SEE AN OPPORTUNITY.

11:30.472 --> 11:32.692
HOW DO YOU FIGURE?

11:32.735 --> 11:35.216
THERE'S A NEW WAVE
COMING INTO D.C.

11:35.259 --> 11:37.958
IF I CAN HELP A CONGRESSMAN
DO SOMETHING OPPORTUNE --

11:38.001 --> 11:39.655
UH, BLOCK AN APPOINTMENT

11:39.699 --> 11:41.962
THAT HIS PARTY IS
DESPERATE TO KILL, SAY --

11:42.005 --> 11:44.051
HE'S IN MY DEBT.

11:44.094 --> 11:46.967
IT'S MONEY IN THE BANK.
THE FUTURE, JANE.

11:47.010 --> 11:48.795
THAT'S WHAT
I'M THINKING ABOUT.

11:48.838 --> 11:52.407
SCREWING DENNIS ABBOTT --
THAT'S JUST ICING ON THE CAKE.

11:52.450 --> 11:54.148
IT WON'T WORK.

11:54.191 --> 11:56.803
WE'LL SEE.YES, WE WILL.

11:56.846 --> 11:58.718
WE SHALL SEE.

11:59.980 --> 12:02.547
I'M REALLY SORRY,
MR. PETERSON.

12:02.591 --> 12:05.333
HE WAS VERY PERSUASIVE.

12:05.376 --> 12:07.814
STACEY... [ SIGHS ]

12:07.857 --> 12:09.163
HAVE YOU SEEN
MY CELL PHONE?

12:09.206 --> 12:11.774
UM...NO.

12:24.918 --> 12:26.484
[ BEEPS ]

12:26.528 --> 12:28.791
[ TYPING ]

12:49.681 --> 12:50.682
MORNING.

12:50.726 --> 12:52.423
[ GROANS, SIGHS ]

12:52.467 --> 12:55.165
HERE.[ MOANS ] THANKS.

12:55.209 --> 12:57.385
DID YOU GET ANYTHING
OFF THE PHONE?

12:57.428 --> 12:59.387
I PULLED ALL OF
PETERSON'S CONTACTS

12:59.430 --> 13:01.650
AND CROSS-REFERENCED THEM
WITH OUR DATABASE.

13:01.693 --> 13:05.132
I CHECKED HIS CALL HISTORY,
HIS E-MAILS, HIS TEXTS...AND?

13:05.175 --> 13:08.788
NOTHING. NOTHING THAT LOOKS LIKE
CONTACT WITH A CARTEL MEMBER.

13:08.831 --> 13:11.181
IF PETERSON'S GETTING
MONEY UNDER THE TABLE,

13:11.225 --> 13:12.835
I DON'T KNOW WHO'S
GIVING IT TO HIM.

13:12.879 --> 13:14.489
CHO AND I COULDN'T
FIND ANYTHING, EITHER.

13:14.532 --> 13:16.273
WE LOOKED INTO OFFSHORE
CORPORATIONS,

13:16.317 --> 13:17.971
THIRD PARTIES' ACCOUNTS.

13:18.014 --> 13:19.450
THERE'S NO SIGN THAT MONEY'S
BEING HIDDEN OR LAUNDERED.

13:19.494 --> 13:20.930
WELL, OF COURSE NOT.

13:20.974 --> 13:22.497
HE KNOWS THAT'S THE FIRST
PLACE SOMEONE WOULD LOOK.

13:22.540 --> 13:24.238
SO WHERE IS HE PUTTING
THE MONEY?

13:24.281 --> 13:26.544
GOT ME. NOTHING ABOUT HIM
REALLY STICKS OUT,

13:26.588 --> 13:28.372
EXCEPT THAT HE'S
SUPER DILIGENT.

13:28.416 --> 13:29.983
WORKS 60 HOURS A WEEK
OR MORE,

13:30.026 --> 13:31.506
AND TWO TO THREE TIMES
A MONTH HE GOES OUT

13:31.549 --> 13:33.769
WITH THE TEAMS ON RAIDS.WHAT KIND OF RAIDS?

13:33.813 --> 13:35.205
E-MAILS MENTION
LOW-LEVEL BUSTS --

13:35.249 --> 13:36.859
NEIGHBORHOOD LABS,
LOCAL DEALERS.

13:36.903 --> 13:38.861
LOW-LEVEL BUSTS? THAT DOESN'T
SOUND LIKE PETERSON.

13:38.905 --> 13:40.732
YEAH, HE WOULDN'T
GET HIS HANDS DIRTY

13:40.776 --> 13:42.691
UNLESS THERE WAS SOMETHING
IN IT FOR HIM.

13:42.734 --> 13:43.866
I'LL BET HE'S SKIMMING.

13:43.910 --> 13:45.346
BY GEORGE, I THINK
SHE'S GOT IT.

13:45.389 --> 13:46.347
SKIMMING WHAT?

13:46.390 --> 13:47.870
WHEN A RAID GOES DOWN,

13:47.914 --> 13:50.003
THE D.E.A. AGENT
ARRESTS THE DEALERS,

13:50.046 --> 13:51.743
AND THEN THEY PROCESS
THE CASH AND THE DRUGS

13:51.787 --> 13:53.267
THAT HAVE BEEN SEIZED.

13:53.310 --> 13:55.269
THE SENIOR AGENT IS SUPPOSED
TO RECORD

13:55.312 --> 13:58.228
THE AMOUNT OF MONEY
AND DRUGS FROM THE CRIME SCENE

13:58.272 --> 14:00.491
BEFORE IT'S PUT INTO EVIDENCE.

14:00.535 --> 14:02.537
UNLESS HE'S TAKING SOME
FOR HIMSELF.

14:02.580 --> 14:04.234
NOBODY KNOWS.

14:04.278 --> 14:06.584
IF THE DRUG DEALER COMPLAINS,
NOBODY BELIEVES HIM.

14:06.628 --> 14:08.630
IT'S KIND OF THE PERFECT CRIME.

14:08.673 --> 14:11.459
$10,000 HERE, $50,000 THERE.
HE COULD HAVE MILLIONS BY NOW.

14:11.502 --> 14:13.330
YEAH, BUT WHERE IS HE
HIDING THE MONEY?

14:13.374 --> 14:15.463
BASED ON THE SECURITY APP
ON PETERSON'S PHONE,

14:15.506 --> 14:17.073
IT LOOKS LIKE HIS HOUSE HAS

14:17.117 --> 14:18.988
A CRAZY ELABORATE
SECURITY SYSTEM.

14:19.032 --> 14:20.642
WELL, THERE'S YOUR ANSWER.
THE MONEY'S IN THE HOUSE.

14:20.685 --> 14:22.252
IF WE COULD GET OUR HANDS
ON THAT CASH

14:22.296 --> 14:23.645
AND PROVE THAT PETERSON'S
STEALING,

14:23.688 --> 14:24.951
WE'D PUT AN END TO THIS
RIGHT NOW.

14:24.994 --> 14:26.691
I DON'T SEE
HOW WE GET IN THE HOUSE.

14:26.735 --> 14:28.868
IT'S LIKE FORT KNOX,
AND WE ONLY HAVE 48 HOURS.

14:28.911 --> 14:31.218
DON'T BE DEFEATIST.
CAN YOU PULL UP THE PLAN

14:31.261 --> 14:34.090
OF THE SECURITY SYSTEM?YEAH, I THINK SO.

14:34.134 --> 14:37.702
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

14:44.492 --> 14:47.930
[ PHONE RINGS ]

14:47.974 --> 14:50.628
[ RINGS ]

14:50.672 --> 14:52.195
BILL PETERSON.

14:52.239 --> 14:54.850
Hello, Mr. Peterson,
this is Missy Brammer.

14:54.894 --> 14:57.461
I'm Congressman Blatt's
legislative director.

14:57.505 --> 15:00.464
I'M FOLLOWING UP ON YOUR
CALL OF A FEW DAYS BACK.

15:00.508 --> 15:03.119
UH, AS I MENTIONED,
I'D VERY MUCH LIKE

15:03.163 --> 15:05.948
TO SPEAK TO CONGRESSMAN BLATT
ABOUT THE NOMINATION

15:05.992 --> 15:08.559
OF LENA ABBOTT
TO THE COMMERCE POST.

15:08.603 --> 15:10.735
Yes, the congressman
was intrigued by your message.

15:10.779 --> 15:12.389
He'd like to know more.

15:12.433 --> 15:15.305
HE'S IN D.C. RIGHT NOW,
AS THE HEARINGS ARE IN TWO DAYS.

15:15.349 --> 15:17.960
Could you and I meet
this evening to discuss it?

15:18.004 --> 15:20.223
YEAH, WELL, THAT'D BE FINE.Good.

15:20.267 --> 15:22.573
8:00 P.M. AT THE WAGON WHEEL
ON ALAMO.

15:22.617 --> 15:23.879
I'll make a reservation.

15:23.923 --> 15:25.272
I'LL SEE YOU THEN.

15:25.315 --> 15:27.927
[ HANGS UP PHONE,
REMOVES PEN CAP ]

15:34.107 --> 15:37.066
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

15:37.110 --> 15:39.982
THE GOOD NEWS IS PETERSON'S
HOUSE IS ONLY ONE FLOOR

15:40.026 --> 15:41.723
AND IS EASILY ACCESSED
FROM THE STREET.

15:41.766 --> 15:43.072
WELL, WHAT'S THE BAD NEWS?

15:43.116 --> 15:44.769
THERE ARE 17
SECURITY CAMERAS,

15:44.813 --> 15:46.815
SIX MOTION SENSORS,
AND ONE CAT.

15:46.858 --> 15:49.339
I HATE CATS. THEY ALWAYS
TRY TO JUMP ON ME.

15:49.383 --> 15:51.167
OH, WHAT ABOUT
THE SECURITY SYSTEM?

15:51.211 --> 15:52.690
I DOWNLOADED AN APP
FROM HIS PHONE

15:52.734 --> 15:54.257
THAT MONITORS
THE CAMERAS.

15:54.301 --> 15:55.650
I CAN HACK INTO
THE FORENSIC SOFTWARE

15:55.693 --> 15:57.478
AND GET AT THE ROOT FOLDERS.

15:57.521 --> 15:59.088
IF HE CHECKS IN REMOTELY, IT'LL
LOOK LIKE NO ONE'S IN THE HOUSE,

15:59.132 --> 16:00.785
BUT I'LL NEED TO DO IT
FROM HERE.

16:06.139 --> 16:07.488
CAN YOU TURN OFF THE ALARM?

16:07.531 --> 16:09.055
YOU'LL NEED TO DO THAT
AT THE HOUSE.

16:09.098 --> 16:11.013
I CAN'T DO IT WITH THE PHONE.[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

16:14.321 --> 16:15.626
HI.

16:15.670 --> 16:18.020
I'D LIKE TO SPEAK
TO CHO, PLEASE.

16:18.064 --> 16:19.282
SURE.

16:20.718 --> 16:21.981
CHO.

16:26.420 --> 16:27.638
WHAT'S UP?

16:27.682 --> 16:29.075
SOMETHING'S OBVIOUSLY
GOING ON,

16:29.118 --> 16:30.859
AND I'M HERE TO PROTEST
MY EXCLUSION.

16:30.902 --> 16:32.426
VEGA.

16:32.469 --> 16:34.297
JANE IS PLANNING SOMETHING,
AND I'M PRETTY SURE

16:34.341 --> 16:36.169
IT HAS TO DO WITH WHATEVER'S
GOING ON WITH ABBOTT.

16:36.212 --> 16:37.605
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.I DO, THOUGH.

16:37.648 --> 16:40.129
IF ABBOTT'S IN TROUBLE,
I WANT TO HELP.

16:41.087 --> 16:43.219
NO.

16:43.263 --> 16:45.395
YOU'RE LETTING WYLIE HELP.WYLIE'S DIFFERENT.

16:45.439 --> 16:46.788
I DON'T FEEL RESPONSIBLE
FOR HIM.

16:46.831 --> 16:48.877
YOU'RE NOT RESPONSIBLE
FOR ME.

16:48.920 --> 16:51.488
VEGA, IF THIS GOES WRONG,
IT'S A CAREER KILLER.

16:51.532 --> 16:52.837
YOU'LL BE FINISHED
AT THE F.B.I.

16:52.881 --> 16:54.752
BEFORE YOU EVEN
GET STARTED.

16:54.796 --> 16:56.232
I'LL TAKE THAT RISK.

16:58.104 --> 17:00.062
WHAT WE'RE DISCUSSING INVOLVES
BREAKING ABOUT SEVEN LAWS.

17:00.106 --> 17:02.804
AS LONG AS IT'S ONLY SEVEN.

17:02.847 --> 17:06.721
EITHER I'M A PART
OF THIS TEAM, OR I'M NOT.

17:08.201 --> 17:09.985
WE NEED EYES
ON BILL PETERSON.

17:10.029 --> 17:12.379
WHERE HE'S GOING,
WHAT HE'S DOING.

17:12.422 --> 17:14.424
YOU THINK YOU CAN DO THAT?ABSOLUTELY.

17:14.468 --> 17:15.599
GO.

17:15.643 --> 17:16.905
THANK YOU, SIR.

17:19.212 --> 17:21.040
DON'T CALL ME "SIR."

17:22.128 --> 17:23.868
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

17:23.912 --> 17:27.002
VEGA.SIR.

17:27.046 --> 17:28.308
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

17:28.351 --> 17:29.744
JUST RUNNING AN ERRAND.

17:37.230 --> 17:39.580
JANE, MY OFFICE, PLEASE.

17:39.623 --> 17:40.972
MM.

17:46.065 --> 17:47.370
WHERE'S LENA?

17:47.414 --> 17:48.806
I JUST DROPPED HER OFF
AT THE AIRPORT.

17:48.850 --> 17:51.983
SHE'S HEADED BACK TO D.C.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

17:52.027 --> 17:53.594
WELL, LIKE I SAID, I --

17:53.637 --> 17:55.422
I CAN'T REALLY
LET YOU IN ON IT.

17:55.465 --> 17:57.989
OKAY, I ASSUME
YOU'RE BREAKING

17:58.033 --> 18:00.427
EVERY RULE AND REGULATION
THE F.B.I. HAS.

18:00.470 --> 18:03.343
WELL, THAT'S A LITTLE
OVER THE TOP.

18:03.386 --> 18:05.127
LOOK, I KNOW I SAID
WE'D DO IT YOUR WAY,

18:05.171 --> 18:06.824
BUT I-I'VE CHANGED MY MIND.

18:06.868 --> 18:10.132
I CAN'T HAVE MY PEOPLE TAKING
RISKS LIKE THIS ON MY BEHALF.

18:10.176 --> 18:13.004
I'LL TAKE WHAT COMES.

18:13.048 --> 18:14.658
AND YOUR WIFE?

18:15.964 --> 18:17.400
I THINK I CAN KEEP HER
OUT OF IT.

18:17.444 --> 18:18.575
YOU KNOW THAT'S NOT TRUE.

18:18.619 --> 18:20.838
WHAT YOU DID
AT RIO BRAVO --

18:20.882 --> 18:22.840
YOU RISKED YOUR LIFE TO
TAKE OUT A MASS MURDERER

18:22.884 --> 18:24.842
THAT NO ONE ELSE COULD...

18:24.886 --> 18:26.931
NO ONE ELSE WOULD.

18:26.975 --> 18:28.498
YOU DID THAT
'CAUSE YOU'RE A GOOD MAN.

18:28.542 --> 18:31.501
PETERSON IS NOT A GOOD MAN.

18:31.545 --> 18:33.895
HE'S A GREEDY, CORRUPT
BUREAUCRAT

18:33.938 --> 18:36.593
WITH A VERY HEALTHY SPRINKLING
OF SOCIOPATH ON TOP.

18:36.637 --> 18:38.465
I CAN HANDLE PETERSON.NO, YOU WON'T.

18:38.508 --> 18:40.162
AND IF WE STOP NOW,
YOU'RE GOING TO PRISON,

18:40.206 --> 18:41.990
YOUR WIFE'S GOING TO
LOSE HER CAREER,

18:42.033 --> 18:45.036
AND PETERSON IS ON HIS WAY
TO BEING THE HEAD OF THE D.E.A.

18:45.080 --> 18:48.953
IS THAT WHAT YOU WANT?
IT'S NOT WHAT I WANT.

18:48.997 --> 18:51.521
AND FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,

18:51.565 --> 18:54.611
EVERYONE ELSE FEELS
THE SAME WAY.

18:56.047 --> 18:57.179
IT'S GONNA BE FINE.

18:58.528 --> 19:00.617
CHIN UP.

19:00.661 --> 19:02.053
TRUST.

19:18.069 --> 19:19.506
[ VEHICLE PASSES ]

19:19.549 --> 19:22.465
[ SPEAKING INAUDIBLY ]

19:27.166 --> 19:28.602
[ KEYS JANGLE ]

19:34.564 --> 19:37.001
OBVIOUSLY, THE HEARINGS
ARE THIS WEEK,

19:37.045 --> 19:39.743
AND DENNIS ABBOTT IS
VERY MUCH IN OUR SIGHT.

19:39.787 --> 19:42.485
THE ISSUE OF WHAT HAPPENED
AT RIO BRAVO

19:42.529 --> 19:46.576
WILL BE KEY TO STOPPING
LENA ABBOTT'S CONFIRMATION.

19:46.620 --> 19:49.057
I'M SO GLAD WE'RE
ON THE SAME PAGE.

19:49.100 --> 19:52.495
WELL, A HEARING'S
A TRICKY THING.

19:52.539 --> 19:54.062
REALLY IT'S ABOUT
SHOWMANSHIP.

19:54.105 --> 19:55.890
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]YOU DISPLAY IT --

19:55.933 --> 19:57.544
A LITTLE THEATRICS,
IF YOU WILL.

19:57.587 --> 19:59.415
IT IS D.C., AFTER ALL.

19:59.459 --> 20:01.635
AS IT HAPPENS,
MS. BRAMMER,

20:01.678 --> 20:03.898
I HAVE SOMETHING
YOU CAN USE.

20:03.941 --> 20:06.901
WOULD YOU BE ABLE TO BRING IT
TO THE OFFICE TOMORROW?

20:06.944 --> 20:08.729
I WOULD.

20:08.772 --> 20:10.121
GOOD.

20:10.165 --> 20:11.514
MM.

20:15.866 --> 20:17.825
CHO, IT'S HAPPENING TOMORROW.

20:17.868 --> 20:20.610
WHATEVER YOU'RE PLANNING,
WE HAVE TO DO IT NOW.

20:28.444 --> 20:31.273
I'M CONNECTED TO PETERSON'S
SECURITY SYSTEM.

20:31.317 --> 20:34.189
LOOKS LIKE HE'S GETTING
READY TO LEAVE.[ BEEPING ]

20:34.233 --> 20:36.235
[ STEADY BEEPING ]

20:42.371 --> 20:43.720
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]

20:45.461 --> 20:46.636
[ SEAT BELT CLICKS ]

20:56.298 --> 20:57.604
WYLIE, IT'S YOUR TIME.

20:57.647 --> 20:59.301
JUST GIVE ME A MINUTE.

20:59.345 --> 21:01.695
[ TYPING ]

21:01.738 --> 21:03.392
OKAY, WE'RE GOOD TO GO.

21:03.436 --> 21:06.047
IF PETERSON CHECKS HIS CAMERAS,
HE'LL SEE A STATIC IMAGE

21:06.090 --> 21:08.702
SHOWING NO ACTIVITY
IN OR OUTSIDE THE HOUSE.GREAT.

21:08.745 --> 21:10.791
BUT I CAN ONLY HOLD IT
FOR ABOUT AN HOUR AND A HALF.

21:10.834 --> 21:13.924
WELL, THAT SHOULD GIVE US
ENOUGH TIME.

21:15.230 --> 21:17.406
SO WHAT'S YOUR PLAN?

21:17.450 --> 21:19.278
WELL...PICK THE LOCK,

21:19.321 --> 21:20.670
OPEN THE DOOR,
SEE WHAT HAPPENS.

21:20.714 --> 21:22.585
WHAT'LL HAPPEN IS THE ALARM
WILL GO OFF.

21:22.629 --> 21:24.108
NOT RIGHT AWAY.
ALARMS GIVE YOU

21:24.152 --> 21:25.066
A MINUTE TO 90-SECOND
GRACE PERIOD

21:25.109 --> 21:26.894
BEFORE THEY ALERT ANYONE.

21:26.937 --> 21:29.113
THAT SHOULD GIVE ME ENOUGH TIME
TO FIGURE OUT THE PASS CODE.

21:29.157 --> 21:30.724
FIGURE IT OUT HOW?

21:30.767 --> 21:32.421
THE WAY I FIGURE THINGS OUT.

21:33.857 --> 21:35.990
THAT'S YOUR PLAN?

21:36.033 --> 21:38.035
YEAH, PRETTY MUCH.

21:43.127 --> 21:46.043
[ LOCK CLICKS,
NUMBER PAD BEEPING ]

21:46.087 --> 21:47.436
Cho: 60 SECONDS.[ DOOR CLOSES ]

21:47.480 --> 21:49.046
YEAH, NOTHING LIKE
A LITTLE ADRENALINE

21:49.090 --> 21:50.526
TO GET THE MIND
FIRED UP.

21:50.570 --> 21:52.746
I'M GONNA NEED
SOME QUIET.[ CAT MEOWS ]

21:52.789 --> 21:54.965
CAT ALERT, NINE O'CLOCK.YEAH, I'M NOT TOUCHING THAT.

21:55.009 --> 21:57.359
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

21:57.403 --> 21:59.405
TIME'S RUNNING OUT.

21:59.448 --> 22:00.580
[ MEOWS ]

22:00.623 --> 22:03.060
[ BEEPING ]HAVE A LITTLE FAITH.

22:03.104 --> 22:04.497
[ BEEPS ]THERE. GOT IT.

22:04.540 --> 22:06.020
HOW'D YOU DO THAT?

22:06.063 --> 22:07.326
WELL --WYLIE TEXTED IT TO HIM.

22:07.369 --> 22:08.762
NO, HE DIDN'T.

22:08.805 --> 22:10.111
WHEN HE HACKED INTO
THE SECURITY SYSTEM,

22:10.154 --> 22:11.765
HE SAW PETERSON PUNCH IN
THE CODE.

22:11.808 --> 22:13.157
I SAW YOU LOOKING
AT YOUR PHONE.

22:13.201 --> 22:14.898
LISBON, YOU'RE KILLING
THE MAGIC HERE.

22:14.942 --> 22:16.204
CAN WE GET MOVING?SURE.

22:16.247 --> 22:17.727
REMEMBER, HE'S NOT GONNA
HIDE THE MONEY

22:17.771 --> 22:19.207
IN OR UNDER HIS MATTRESS.

22:19.250 --> 22:20.643
HIDDEN COMPARTMENTS,
FALSE DRAWERS.

22:20.687 --> 22:21.731
ALL OVER IT.

22:57.463 --> 23:00.117
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

23:06.080 --> 23:07.386
[ GROANS ]

23:08.387 --> 23:10.519
[ HOLLOW KNOCK ]

23:51.299 --> 23:54.433
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS,
DOOR OPENS ]

24:29.468 --> 24:31.861
WE GOT GUNS, NO MONEY.

24:31.905 --> 24:34.864
IF THE MONEY'S HERE SOMEPLACE,
WE CAN'T FIND IT.

24:34.908 --> 24:36.344
JANE?

24:36.387 --> 24:38.868
CANDLESTICKS SEEM A LITTLE
ODD, DON'T THEY?

24:38.912 --> 24:40.522
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

24:40.566 --> 24:42.611
I MEAN, FOR A THIN STRIP
OF TEXAS LEATHER LIKE PETERSON.

24:42.655 --> 24:44.831
DOESN'T STRIKE ME
AS THE CANDLESTICK TYPE.

24:44.874 --> 24:46.485
MAYBE HE HIRED A DESIGNER.

24:46.528 --> 24:47.790
MAYBE.

24:52.578 --> 24:54.275
CHINA.

24:57.626 --> 24:59.846
[ CLICKS, WHIRRING ]

25:03.153 --> 25:04.807
OH, THIS IS A PROBLEM.

25:04.851 --> 25:06.766
DON'T YOU KNOW HOW TO OPEN
A SAFE?BIOMETRICS.

25:06.809 --> 25:08.158
WE NEED PETERSON'S
THUMBPRINT TO OPEN THAT.

25:08.202 --> 25:09.943
WELL, WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

25:09.986 --> 25:11.901
OKAY, SO WE GO
TO THE BACKUP PLAN.

25:11.945 --> 25:14.251
WHAT'S THAT?WE HAVE ABOUT 40 MINUTES LEFT.

25:14.295 --> 25:16.732
IF WE CAN'T GET TO PETERSON'S
MONEY, WE'LL USE OUR OWN MONEY.

25:16.776 --> 25:17.907
WHAT MONEY?

25:17.951 --> 25:19.735
UH, WYLIE, I NEED YOU

25:19.779 --> 25:22.390
TO GET INTO THE EVIDENCE ROOM
AND GET US SOME CASH.

25:22.433 --> 25:24.348
HOW MUCH?

25:24.392 --> 25:26.960
AT LEAST A MILLION DOLLARS.
TWO WOULD BE BETTER.

25:27.003 --> 25:30.180
THAT'S...BIG. I'M -- I'M NOT
SURE HOW I'D DO THAT.

25:30.224 --> 25:33.488
DO YOUR BEST.
YEAH, IT'S VERY IMPORTANT.

25:33.532 --> 25:36.143
I DON'T HAVE CLEARANCE
FOR THAT.

25:36.186 --> 25:38.188
LET ME, UH...

25:38.232 --> 25:40.364
LET ME THINK.

25:43.716 --> 25:45.500
I'LL GET BACK TO YOU.

25:50.636 --> 25:51.854
SIR.

25:51.898 --> 25:53.508
WHAT IS IT?

25:53.552 --> 25:55.466
YOU KNOW HOW JANE SAID
HE WOULDN'T NEED YOUR HELP?

25:55.510 --> 25:57.468
[ SIGHS ][ STIRRER CLINKS ]

25:57.512 --> 26:00.254
HE LIED, DIDN'T HE?

26:01.821 --> 26:03.866
[ PHONE RINGS ]

26:03.910 --> 26:05.346
WHAT'S UP, WYLIE?

26:05.389 --> 26:06.739
VEGA, IS PETERSON STILL
AT BLATT'S OFFICE?

26:06.782 --> 26:08.262
Yeah. He just got there.

26:08.305 --> 26:10.046
ANY CHANCE HE'LL GO
TO WORK WHEN HE'S DONE?

26:10.090 --> 26:11.961
I CALLED HIS OFFICE. THEY SAID
HE'S NOT EXPECTED IN TODAY. WHY?

26:12.005 --> 26:14.007
I'M GOING TO SAN ANTONIO.[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

26:14.050 --> 26:16.096
It's gonna take me about
40 minutes to get there.

26:16.139 --> 26:18.751
IF PETERSON LEAVES IN THE NEXT
HALF AN HOUR, STALL HIM, OKAY?

26:18.794 --> 26:21.492
STALL HIM? THE--
UH, OKAY.

26:22.450 --> 26:23.669
[ PHONE BEEPS ]

26:42.339 --> 26:45.125
[ STARTS ENGINE ]

26:49.172 --> 26:50.609
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

26:55.875 --> 26:57.485
[ Whispers ] STALL HIM.

26:57.528 --> 27:00.009
[ Normal voice ]
STALL HIM. [ SIGHS ]

27:02.229 --> 27:04.318
STALL HIM.

27:06.189 --> 27:09.018
[ BREATHES SHARPLY ][ ENGINE REVS ]

27:12.805 --> 27:14.545
OH, MY GOD, I AM SO SORRY!

27:14.589 --> 27:16.809
I'LL GET YOU MY INSURANCE!

27:22.771 --> 27:23.990
AHH...

27:24.033 --> 27:26.427
[ HUFFS ][ PAPERS RUSTLING ]

27:26.470 --> 27:28.081
DID YOU SEE THAT?

27:28.124 --> 27:29.604
COULD HAVE BEEN WORSE.
YOU STOP SHORT?

27:29.648 --> 27:32.868
NO, I DIDN'T STOP SHORT!
SHE RAN RIGHT INTO ME!

27:32.912 --> 27:35.044
I'M SO SORRY!
ARE YOU OKAY?

27:35.088 --> 27:36.959
HOW DO I KNOW?
YOU RAN RIGHT INTO ME!

27:37.003 --> 27:39.440
YOU'LL WANT TO FILL OUT
A REPORT FOR YOUR INSURANCE.

27:39.483 --> 27:43.052
[ SIGHS ] OH, FOR GOD SAKE!

27:53.976 --> 27:56.631
[ PAPERS RUSTLING ]

27:56.675 --> 27:59.025
[ SIGHS ]
IS THERE A PROBLEM?

27:59.068 --> 28:01.244
I -- I KNOW I JUST
GOT THEM RENEWED.

28:01.288 --> 28:03.159
I PUT THEM IN HERE.
I TOOK OUT THE OLD ONES,

28:03.203 --> 28:05.292
PUT THE NEW ONES IN.MISS?

28:05.335 --> 28:07.598
I JUST FEEL SO TERRIBLE
ABOUT THIS.

28:07.642 --> 28:08.774
I KNOW YOU!

28:08.817 --> 28:10.819
YOU'RE ONE OF ABBOTT'S
PEOPLE.

28:13.474 --> 28:14.780
AGENT PETERSON?

28:14.823 --> 28:17.434
OH, NOW I AM REALLY
EMBARRASSED.

28:17.478 --> 28:19.306
I AM SO SORRY, SIR.
UH --

28:19.349 --> 28:20.829
THE SUN WAS IN MY EYES

28:20.873 --> 28:22.570
AND I THOUGHT YOU WERE
A LOT FURTHER AWAY FROM ME.

28:22.613 --> 28:24.615
LOOK, UH, JUST --
JUST FORGET ABOUT IT.

28:24.659 --> 28:26.922
OH, NO, SIR, WE --
WE COULD NEVER DO THAT.

28:26.966 --> 28:30.012
[ GASPS ] THERE IS SO MUCH
DAMAGE TO YOUR CAR HERE.I'M NOT WORRIED ABOUT IT.

28:30.056 --> 28:32.101
WE REALLY SHOULD FILL OUT
A REPORT, THOUGH.

28:32.145 --> 28:35.365
YOUR CAR REALLY LOOKS TERRIBLE.I'M IN A HURRY!

28:36.497 --> 28:37.846
[ TIRES SCREECH ]

28:40.283 --> 28:42.068
I tried to stop him,
but he wouldn't stay.

28:42.111 --> 28:43.243
WHICH WAY'S HE HEADING?

28:43.286 --> 28:44.766
EAST. HE'S HEADED
YOUR WAY.

28:44.810 --> 28:46.115
Well, how far are you?

28:46.159 --> 28:47.943
ABOUT 15 MINUTES.
HOW FAR IS WYLIE?

28:47.987 --> 28:49.205
ABOUT 15 MINUTES.

29:03.393 --> 29:04.873
I GOT HERE AS FAST
AS I COULD.

29:04.917 --> 29:06.440
[ Chewing ] THANK YOU.

29:09.748 --> 29:11.793
GOOD LUCK. BYE.

29:34.337 --> 29:35.686
[ BEEPING ]

29:35.730 --> 29:39.342
[ STEADY BEEPING ]

29:41.780 --> 29:43.346
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

29:43.390 --> 29:44.695
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

29:44.739 --> 29:47.873
[ NUMBER PAD BEEPING ]

29:48.917 --> 29:53.008
[ BEEPING, CAT MEOWS ]

30:02.539 --> 30:04.019
OBVIOUSLY THE ISSUE
WITH PROTECTED ZONES

30:04.063 --> 30:05.891
IS COLORED BY MONEY,
BUT WE'RE GONNA HAVE TO --

30:05.934 --> 30:06.979
MRS. ABBOTT.

30:07.022 --> 30:08.807
DENNIS?

30:08.850 --> 30:10.765
[ LAUGHS ]LINDA, I'LL CATCH UP
WITH YOU LATER.

30:10.809 --> 30:14.464
OH...BABY. MMM.

30:14.508 --> 30:16.075
WHAT ARE YOU DOING IN D.C.?

30:16.118 --> 30:18.817
WELL, I WANTED TO SEE YOU.

30:18.860 --> 30:20.383
AND I KNOW YOU'RE SCARED.

30:20.427 --> 30:22.211
MORE LIKE TERRIFIED.

30:22.255 --> 30:23.691
WELL, DON'T BE.

30:23.734 --> 30:25.649
I TRUST JANE.

30:25.693 --> 30:27.303
AND HE HASN'T LET ME DOWN
SO FAR.

30:27.347 --> 30:29.131
DENNIS, WE NEED A MIRACLE.

30:29.175 --> 30:32.308
LISTEN.
YOU WILL BE CONFIRMED.

30:32.352 --> 30:34.397
AND WE'LL BE TOGETHER.

30:34.441 --> 30:37.879
[ SIGHS ] I HAVE TO GO.
THE HEARING'S ABOUT TO START.

30:37.923 --> 30:39.402
OKAY, I'LL WALK YOU IN.

30:39.446 --> 30:41.752
I HAVE SOMETHING TO DO
INSIDE ANYWAY.

30:48.150 --> 30:49.673
ABBOTT.HMM?

30:49.717 --> 30:51.023
FUNNY MEETING YOU HERE.

30:51.066 --> 30:52.720
WELL, I COULD SAY
THE SAME THING, BILL.

30:52.763 --> 30:54.243
I GUESS YOU HAVEN'T HEARD.

30:54.287 --> 30:57.159
IT'S NOT OFFICIAL YET,
BUT I'M GONNA BE A WITNESS

30:57.203 --> 30:59.292
AT YOUR WIFE'S HEARING.

30:59.335 --> 31:00.815
AH. WELL, WHO DID THAT?

31:00.859 --> 31:02.904
BLATT.

31:02.948 --> 31:04.253
REPRESENTATIVE JULES BLATT

31:04.297 --> 31:06.125
PUT YOUR NAME ON THE LIST
TO BE A WITNESS?

31:06.168 --> 31:08.779
I HAVE EVIDENCE HE THINKS
PEOPLE SHOULD HEAR ABOUT.

31:08.823 --> 31:10.259
I THINK YOU KNOW
WHAT IT IS.

31:10.303 --> 31:12.958
EVIDENCE, HUH?
EVIDENCE THAT YOU BROUGHT HIM?

31:13.001 --> 31:15.308
WHAT IS THIS, ABBOTT?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

31:15.351 --> 31:18.050
YOU KNOW, MAYBE I SHOULD
TALK TO BLATT.

31:18.093 --> 31:20.139
YOU SEE, I HAVE EVIDENCE,
TOO.

31:20.182 --> 31:21.401
YEAH. TAKE A LOOK.

31:21.444 --> 31:23.925
NOW THAT'S NICE.

31:23.969 --> 31:28.364
[ LAUGHS ] OKAY, THAT'S
THE BEST ONE RIGHT THERE.

31:28.408 --> 31:30.105
WHAT -- BILL?

31:31.106 --> 31:33.065
[ KNOB CLICKS, DOOR THUDS ]

31:33.108 --> 31:35.110
WAIT -- BILL?

31:35.154 --> 31:37.330
[ KNOB CLICKS, DOOR THUDS ]

31:41.377 --> 31:43.902
SEEMS WE BOTH HAVE SECRETS.

31:43.945 --> 31:45.773
CUTE KITTY, BY THE WAY.

31:45.816 --> 31:47.993
[ GRUNTS ]

31:52.084 --> 31:53.346
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

31:53.389 --> 31:55.696
AHH... [ SIGHS ]

31:55.739 --> 31:57.045
PUT YOUR HANDS UP.

31:57.089 --> 31:58.394
YOU THINK I'M WEARING
A WIRE?

31:58.438 --> 32:00.614
UP!

32:00.657 --> 32:02.529
COME ON, BILL!

32:02.572 --> 32:05.619
THIS IS JUST A CONVERSATION
BETWEEN TWO OLD FRIENDS, RIGHT?

32:05.662 --> 32:08.013
YOU BROKE INTO MY HOME.

32:08.056 --> 32:11.103
I HAVE PEOPLE THAT WILL ACCOUNT
FOR EVERY MINUTE OF MY TIME.

32:11.146 --> 32:12.800
IF IT WASN'T YOU,
THEN IT WAS JANE

32:12.843 --> 32:14.367
OR ONE OF THOSE OTHER
IDIOTS.

32:14.410 --> 32:16.760
THAT'S A CRIME, NOT TO
MENTION ILLEGAL SEARCH.

32:16.804 --> 32:20.895
WELL, THAT'LL BE
FOR THE D.A. TO SORT OUT.

32:20.939 --> 32:24.377
BUT IT WILL GET THE ATTENTION
OF THE INSPECTOR GENERAL.

32:24.420 --> 32:26.640
AND THERE WILL BE
AN INTERNAL INVESTIGATION,

32:26.683 --> 32:28.816
AND THEY'LL LOOK INTO
ALL OF YOUR OLD BUSTS

32:28.859 --> 32:32.559
AND REALIZE THAT YOU HAVE BEEN
A THIEF FOR 20 YEARS.

32:35.475 --> 32:37.694
I HAVE YOU, BILL.

32:37.738 --> 32:41.133
I HAVE YOU BY
THE SHORT AND CURLIES.

32:42.525 --> 32:44.005
OKAY.

32:44.049 --> 32:45.833
[ LAUGHS ]

32:45.876 --> 32:49.271
OKAY. FINE.

32:49.315 --> 32:50.664
TAKE HALF.

32:50.707 --> 32:53.580
WE BOTH WALK AWAY.
THIS IS OVER.

32:53.623 --> 32:56.017
WOW. HALF. HMM.

32:56.061 --> 32:57.236
HOW MUCH IS HALF?

32:57.279 --> 32:58.411
ABOUT 800.

32:58.454 --> 33:01.675
SO YOU'RE OFFERING ME
$800,000

33:01.718 --> 33:03.285
OF THE CASH THAT YOU'VE
BEEN SKIMMING?

33:03.329 --> 33:04.939
YOU'RE NOT GETTING
A DIME MORE.

33:04.983 --> 33:06.593
I DON'T WANT ANY MORE.

33:06.636 --> 33:08.769
HELLO AGAIN, AGENT PETERSON.

33:11.815 --> 33:14.775
I HAVE ALL I NEED.

33:17.256 --> 33:18.431
[ DOOR OPENS ]

33:21.564 --> 33:22.870
[ SIGHS ]

33:22.913 --> 33:25.612
IT DOESN'T MATTER
WHAT YOU DO TO ME.

33:25.655 --> 33:27.309
IT CAN'T HELP.WHY NOT?

33:27.353 --> 33:28.702
BLATT HAS THE BULLET.

33:28.745 --> 33:31.487
THE BULLET YOU SHOT
INTO THAT ZETA'S HEAD.

33:31.531 --> 33:33.750
BULLET.

33:33.794 --> 33:35.926
WAS THAT THE EVIDENCE
YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT?

33:35.970 --> 33:38.842
THAT'S RIGHT. AND WHEN BLATT
GETS DONE WITH IT,

33:38.886 --> 33:42.107
YOUR WIFE CAN KISS
HER NEW JOB GOOD-BYE.

33:42.150 --> 33:44.718
AND YOU'RE GOING TO PRISON,
MY FRIEND.

33:44.761 --> 33:46.372
ABBOTT, PETERSON, VEGA.HEY.

33:46.415 --> 33:47.808
UH, GOOD TO SEE YOU ALL.

33:47.851 --> 33:49.810
ALL ME TO INTRODUCE
CONGRESSMAN BLATT'S

33:49.853 --> 33:53.161
LEGISLATIVE DIRECTOR,
MISSY, UM...

33:53.205 --> 33:55.946
UH...I'M SORRY. WHAT IS IT?UH, BRAMMER.

33:55.990 --> 33:58.079
SORRY. MISSY BRAMMER.[ CHUCKLES ]

33:58.123 --> 34:00.081
UH, YOU SAID YOU HAD
A CONSTITUENT WHO HAD TO SEE ME?

34:00.125 --> 34:02.301
YES, MISS BRAMMER.
THIS IS BILL PETERSON.

34:02.344 --> 34:06.218
HE IS ONE OF THE CONGRESSMAN'S
MOST ENTHUSIASTIC SUPPORTERS.

34:06.261 --> 34:07.306
OH, HOW DO YOU DO?

34:07.349 --> 34:09.438
YEAH, WAIT -- NO.

34:09.482 --> 34:12.180
THIS ISN'T RIGHT.I'M SORRY?

34:12.224 --> 34:15.096
THERE'S BEEN A MISTAKE.
I MET MISSY BRAMMER

34:15.140 --> 34:16.532
TWO DAYS AGO IN SAN ANTONIO.

34:16.576 --> 34:18.360
Jane: WELL, THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE,
BECAUSE

34:18.404 --> 34:21.537
MISS BRAMMER'S BEEN HERE
IN D.C. ALL WEEK

34:21.581 --> 34:23.365
PREPARING FOR THE HEARINGS.

34:23.409 --> 34:25.411
UH, WHICH I'M GONNA BE
LATE FOR IF I DON'T HURRY.OKAY.

34:25.454 --> 34:27.891
NICE TO MEET YOU ALL.
MR. PETERSON.

34:27.935 --> 34:31.156
HEY. WAIT --

34:31.199 --> 34:32.461
HMM.

34:32.505 --> 34:34.159
NO, NO, NO.

34:34.202 --> 34:36.726
SHE RETURNED MY CALL
FROM BLATT'S OFFICE.

34:36.770 --> 34:38.859
HI. MY CELL PHONE
JUST DIED.

34:38.902 --> 34:40.991
COULD I USE ONE OF YOURS?SURE. MISSY'S OUT OF TOWN.
YOU CAN USE HERS.

34:41.035 --> 34:44.038
OH. THANK YOU VERY MUCH.YOU'RE WELCOME.

34:44.082 --> 34:45.953
[ RINGS ]

34:45.996 --> 34:47.389
BILL PETERSON.

34:47.433 --> 34:52.133
HELLO, MR. PETERSON,
THIS IS MISSY BRAMMER.

34:52.177 --> 34:54.570
I'M CONGRESSMAN BLATT'S
LEGISLATIVE DIRECTOR.

34:54.614 --> 34:57.921
I MET HER! IN BLATT'S OFFICE.

34:57.965 --> 35:00.010
SORRY, EVERYBODY.
PEST CONTROL.

35:00.054 --> 35:02.056
WE NEED THE OFFICE
FOR 20 MINUTES.

35:02.100 --> 35:05.233
ALL RIGHT. EVERYBODY OUT.
THEY GOT TO SPRAY.

35:12.588 --> 35:15.896
[ DOOR CLOSES,
ZIPPERS UNZIPPING ]

35:29.127 --> 35:32.478
HEY. HELLO.COME IN.

35:34.132 --> 35:35.568
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

35:35.611 --> 35:37.178
[ SIGHS ] I GOT SOMETHING
FOR YOU.

35:37.222 --> 35:38.571
THANK YOU.

35:40.921 --> 35:42.314
HERE WE GO.

35:47.928 --> 35:49.234
[ CLATTERS ]

35:50.452 --> 35:52.062
BILL?

35:52.106 --> 35:55.109
I CAN'T TELL YOU HOW MUCH
IT MEANS TO ME TO SAY THIS.

35:55.153 --> 35:57.111
YOU'RE UNDER ARREST.

35:57.155 --> 35:58.286
[ GASPS ]

35:58.330 --> 35:59.853
[ HANDCUFFS CLICKING ]

35:59.896 --> 36:02.203
WONDERFUL TO SEE
THE GOVERNMENT AT WORK.

36:02.247 --> 36:03.639
[ SIGHS ]

36:11.256 --> 36:13.345
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

36:13.388 --> 36:15.825
GUYS, LET ME DRIVE YOU
TO THE AIRPORT.

36:15.869 --> 36:17.218
NO.NAH, YOU'VE DONE
ENOUGH ALREADY.

36:17.262 --> 36:20.003
WELL, THANK YOU
FOR EVERYTHING.

36:20.047 --> 36:22.223
AW... [ LAUGHS ][ LAUGHS ]

36:22.267 --> 36:24.051
YOU KNOW WHAT? THAT WAS
SOME GOOD, CLEAN FUN.

36:24.094 --> 36:26.706
LIKE OLD TIMES.JUST LIKE OLD TIMES.

36:26.749 --> 36:29.535
PETE, HOLD THE DOOR
A SEC.

36:29.578 --> 36:31.232
HE TELLS ME YOU GOT
A SWEETHEART.

36:31.276 --> 36:32.494
THAT LITTLE BRUNETTE?

36:32.538 --> 36:33.843
THAT IS TRUE.

36:33.887 --> 36:36.237
MM-HMM.
DON'T SCREW IT UP, PATRICK.

36:36.281 --> 36:37.804
I'LL TRY NOT TO.

36:37.847 --> 36:39.632
LIFE'S TOO SHORT.

36:41.024 --> 36:43.853
[ CHUCKLES ]
MM.

36:43.897 --> 36:44.941
SEE YA.

36:44.985 --> 36:47.640
BYE.COME ON...

36:50.860 --> 36:55.474
[ COUNTRY ROCK PLAYING,
INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

36:56.823 --> 36:58.781
[ CORK POPS, LAUGHTER ]HO, HO!

36:58.825 --> 37:02.089
SCARED ME THERE.
NOW DON'T SPILL ANY.

37:02.132 --> 37:03.351
UM...PLASTIC CUPS?

37:03.395 --> 37:04.657
[ LAUGHING ]

37:04.700 --> 37:08.051
OKAY. A TOAST.

37:08.095 --> 37:09.836
TO FRIENDS.

37:09.879 --> 37:13.753
THANK YOU FOR...
ALL...

37:13.796 --> 37:15.885
WE ARE FOREVER
IN YOUR DEBT.

37:15.929 --> 37:17.626
YES, YES.[ LAUGHTER ]

37:17.670 --> 37:19.628
WE ARE FOREVER IN YOUR DEBT.
I-I MAKE HORRIBLE SPEECHES.

37:19.672 --> 37:20.977
I'M SO SORRY.CHEERS. CHEERS.

37:21.021 --> 37:22.370
CHEERS.CHEERS.

37:22.414 --> 37:23.763
CHEERS.CHEERS.

37:23.806 --> 37:25.460
[ LAUGHTER ]

37:26.722 --> 37:28.289
LET'S GO CHECK OUT
THAT WAFFLE TRUCK.

37:28.333 --> 37:30.509
OH, DEFINITELY.

37:30.552 --> 37:33.512
♪♪♪

37:35.078 --> 37:37.255
SO HOW FAST WERE YOU GOING WHEN
YOU DROVE TO SAN ANTONIO?

37:37.298 --> 37:39.605
LIKE A HUNDRED MILLION
MILES AN HOUR.

37:39.648 --> 37:41.433
ROUGHLY. HOW FAST WERE YOU
GOING WHEN YOU RAMMED

37:41.476 --> 37:43.261
THE BACK OF PETERSON'S CAR?

37:43.304 --> 37:45.915
LIKE 3 MILES AN HOUR.STILL, I BET IT WAS
PRETTY COOL.

37:45.959 --> 37:48.222
IT WAS.
IT WAS REALLY COOL.

37:50.833 --> 37:53.053
YOU KNOW, I DON'T WANT A WAFFLE.
YOU WANT TO DANCE?

37:55.185 --> 37:57.318
NO. NO, I'M --
I'M A TERRIBLE DANCER.

37:57.362 --> 37:58.885
I --OH, COME ON.

37:58.928 --> 38:00.539
WHAT DO YOU HAVE TO LOSE,
WYLIE?

38:00.582 --> 38:02.323
[ STAMMERS ]COME ON. LET'S GO.

38:02.367 --> 38:03.629
OKAY, BUT YOU CAN'T LAUGH.

38:03.672 --> 38:05.108
NO PROMISES.

38:05.152 --> 38:09.025
WELL, SINCE EVERYTHING
IS CLEARED UP WITH LENA,

38:09.069 --> 38:10.766
I'LL BE MOVING
IN A COUPLE OF MONTHS.

38:10.810 --> 38:12.464
WORK FROM THE D.C. OFFICE.

38:12.507 --> 38:15.423
SO YOU KNOW WHAT THAT MEANS.
IT'S YOU.

38:17.033 --> 38:18.208
WHAT IS?

38:18.252 --> 38:21.081
THE UNIT. IT'S YOURS.

38:22.038 --> 38:23.475
YOU'LL BE IN CHARGE.

38:23.518 --> 38:25.390
I TALKED
TO THE REGIONAL OFFICE,

38:25.433 --> 38:27.305
I TALKED TO
THE ASSISTANT DIRECTOR,

38:27.348 --> 38:29.742
AND EVERYONE AGREES.

38:29.785 --> 38:32.092
YOU'VE EARNED IT, KIMBALL.

38:32.135 --> 38:34.399
AND I THINK YOU'RE GOING TO DO
A GREAT JOB AT IT.

38:38.707 --> 38:40.318
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

38:40.361 --> 38:41.536
[ LAUGHS ]

38:41.580 --> 38:42.929
THANK YOU, SIR.

38:42.972 --> 38:45.932
NO. THANK YOU.

38:45.975 --> 38:49.501
WELL, SINCE THAT'S SETTLED,
I THINK I AM GOING TO DANCE

38:49.544 --> 38:54.419
WITH THE NEXT UNDERSECRETARY
OF THE DEPARTMENT OF COMMERCE.

38:54.462 --> 38:56.464
GET ON THE DANCE FLOOR, BABY.
COME ON.

38:56.508 --> 38:59.380
[ LAUGHTER ]

38:59.424 --> 39:00.947
CONGRATULATIONS, CHO.

39:00.990 --> 39:02.122
THANK YOU.

39:02.165 --> 39:03.863
YOU DESERVE IT.MM.

39:07.214 --> 39:09.042
I'M GONNA GO GET
ANOTHER TACO.

39:09.085 --> 39:11.740
OKAY.

39:11.784 --> 39:15.353
♪♪♪

39:15.396 --> 39:18.747
YOU KNOW, WE NEVER FINISHED
OUR CONVERSATION.

39:18.791 --> 39:21.402
NO, IT GOT BUSY.

39:21.446 --> 39:23.056
LIFE THROWS YOU CURVE BALLS.

39:23.099 --> 39:24.710
ARE WE TALKING ABOUT
BASEBALL NOW?

39:24.753 --> 39:27.452
I'M SERIOUS. I WANT US
TO BE STRONG TOGETHER.

39:27.495 --> 39:30.063
WE ARE, AREN'T WE?

39:30.106 --> 39:33.458
I LOVE YOU,
AND I ALSO LOVE WHAT I DO.

39:33.501 --> 39:35.460
YOU CAN'T BE JEALOUS
OF THAT.

39:35.503 --> 39:37.244
OH, IT'S NOT THAT.

39:37.287 --> 39:38.637
WHAT IS IT?

39:44.773 --> 39:46.340
WHAT?

39:47.994 --> 39:49.822
I DON'T WANT TO LOSE YOU.

39:51.214 --> 39:54.392
I DON'T KNOW
HOW I WOULD REACT.

39:55.523 --> 39:56.872
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
LOSE ME.

39:56.916 --> 39:58.787
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.

39:58.831 --> 40:00.572
NOBODY KNOWS
WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN.

40:00.615 --> 40:03.270
YOU COULD DIE TOMORROW.
I COULD.

40:03.313 --> 40:07.187
WE NEED TO FOCUS ON
WHAT'S GOING ON RIGHT NOW.

40:07.230 --> 40:08.667
RIGHT HERE. IT'S GOOD.

40:08.710 --> 40:12.061
IT IS VERY, VERY GOOD.

40:13.280 --> 40:14.934
YEAH.

40:16.283 --> 40:17.458
OKAY.

40:17.502 --> 40:18.503
ARE YOU SURE?

40:18.546 --> 40:20.330
YEAH.

40:21.810 --> 40:23.812
DO YOU WANT TO DANCE?

40:23.856 --> 40:25.553
HERE? IN FRONT OF EVERYONE?

40:25.597 --> 40:27.555
SURE.

40:27.599 --> 40:30.515
OKAY, ONE DANCE.TWO.

40:30.558 --> 40:32.952
EVERYTHING IS A NEGOTIATION
WITH YOU.

40:32.995 --> 40:34.127
MM.

40:36.216 --> 40:38.174
COME ON.

40:38.218 --> 40:41.743
♪♪♪
